    "markdown": "---\ntitle: Segregation and diversity in Albuquerque\nsubtitle: Modeling with R and tidycensus\ncategories:\n  - GIS\n  - R\n  - Data Science\nexecute:\n  cache: true\ndate: \"2025-05-09\"\n---\n\n# Modeling segregation and diversity\n\n\n\nAlbuquerque had 565K citizens according to the 2020 census[^1], with an estimated 2023 population of 560K, representing a slight decline. As a comparison, Atlanta, Georgia, with a population under 500K in 2020, is estimated to have grown nearly 2.43% to 511K in 2023. This article will compare these two cities of comparable size and geography in terms of income, segregation, and racial diversity. Both cities are the largest in their states.\n\n[^1]: <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_United_States_cities_by_population>\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(tidycensus)\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(segregation)\nlibrary(tigris)\nlibrary(sf)\noptions(tigris_use_cache=TRUE)\n```\n:::\n\n\n# Data Preparation\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nnm_acs_data <- get_acs(\n  geography = \"tract\",\n  variables = c(\n    white = \"B03002_003\",\n    black = \"B03002_004\",\n    native = \"B03002_005\",\n    asian = \"B03002_006\",\n    hispanic = \"B03002_012\"\n  ),\n  state = \"NM\",\n  geometry = T,\n  year = 2023\n)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nGetting data from the 2019-2023 5-year ACS\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nDownloading feature geometry from the Census website.  To cache shapefiles for use in future sessions, set `options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE)`.\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nga_acs_data <- get_acs(\n  geography = \"tract\",\n  variables = c(\n    white = \"B03002_003\",\n    black = \"B03002_004\",\n    native = \"B03002_005\",\n    asian = \"B03002_006\",\n    hispanic = \"B03002_012\"\n  ),\n  state = \"GA\",\n  geometry = T,\n  year = 2023\n)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nGetting data from the 2019-2023 5-year ACS\nDownloading feature geometry from the Census website.  To cache shapefiles for use in future sessions, set `options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE)`.\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nus_urban_areas <- get_acs(\n  geography = \"urban area\",\n  variables = \"B01001_001\",\n  geometry = T,\n  year = 2019,\n  survey = \"acs1\"\n) |> \n  filter(estimate >= 500000) |> \n  transmute(urban_name = str_remove(NAME,\n                                    fixed(\", NM Urbanized Area (2010)\")))\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nGetting data from the 2019 1-year ACS\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nThe 1-year ACS provides data for geographies with populations of 65,000 and greater.\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nDownloading feature geometry from the Census website.  To cache shapefiles for use in future sessions, set `options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE)`.\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n  |                                                                            \n  |                                                                      |   0%\n  |                                                                            \n  |                                                                      |   1%\n  |                                                                            \n  |=                                                                     |   1%\n  |                                                                            \n  |=                                                                     |   2%\n  |                                                                            \n  |==                                                                    |   2%\n  |                                                                            \n  |==                                                                